    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make Altering Property Borders without Consent a Specific Criminal Offence",
        "additional_details": "A new law is urgently required to protect the rights of individuals, families and the impact on them when their borders have been trespassed/encroached. Many property owners are losing out on part of their borders and have part of their land obstructed, preventing them from extending on their own property. The current legislation does not adequately cover neighbours unlawfully altering/occupying another neighbours land. The police should be able to intervene at the early stages and bring criminal charges.",
        "background": "The Government to pass a law to make it a criminal offence for neighbours to alter property boundaries by moving borders, erecting fences, walls, extending roofs, obstructing, disrupting on private land. It can result in costly civil disputes, offenders are often well off.",
